com.wingfoot.xml
Class XMLFactory

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.wingfoot.xml.XMLFactory
public class XMLFactory
extends java.lang.Object

A Factory pattern that aids in parsing or writing a XML document. The current XML documents supported are WSDL and XML Schema.

parse

public static XMLHolder parse(byte[] payload,
                              java.lang.String location)
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              SchemaException,
                              WSDLException,
                              java.lang.Exception
Takes a payload representing a XML document and encapsulates it as a Holder. The method is able to determine the kind of XML document and returns back the proper Holder.
Parameters:
payload - XML document represented as a byte array. The two supported XML documents are WSDL and XML Schema.
location - String identifying the location where the XML documented is located. It is either a location on the local file system or on a web server. The location is used in instances where the XML document contains an import statement and has (incorrectly) with a relative value in the location attribute. The absoluteURI is then determined using theis location parameter.
Returns:
Holder the XML document encapsulated as as Holder. Depending on the kind of payload the Holder is either an instance of WSDLHolder or SchemaHolder.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if an error occurs while processing the payload.
SchemaException - if the XML document is a schema and an error occurs while processing the schema
WSDLException - if the XML document is a WSDL and an error occurs while processing the WSDL
java.lang.Exception - if any other occurs while processing the payload.

parse

public static XMLHolder parse(java.lang.Class classToConvert,
                              Options options,
                              int holderType)
                       throws SchemaException,
                              WSDLException,
                              java.lang.Exception
Takes a Java class and returns a XMLHolder representation of it. The holderType parameter is used to determine whether to return a WSDLHolder or a SchemaHolder.
Parameters:
class - - The java class to convert into XMLHolder
options - - This options class encapsulates user input that affects the output of the XMLHolder
holderType - - HolderType is used to determine which type of XMLHolder to return. Currently we only support WSDLHolder, however, it is easy to extend this to return any type of holder.
Returns:
XMLHolder The appropriate XMLHolder is returned depending on the holderType specified
Throws:
SchemaException - a Schema Exception is thrown if any error occurs while processing a schema
WSDLException - a WSDL Exception is thrown if any error occurs while processing a WSDL
java.lang.Exception - an Exception is thrown if any other error occurs

Utility method that reads the content of a file represented by location.
Parameters:
location - String that contains the location of a XML document. The location is either a file in the local file system or a resource on a web server.

The location must be a absolute location (not a relative URI or location).

Returns:
byte[] byte representation of the resource.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if any error occurs while reading from the resource.

toXML

public static SerializedHolder[] toXML(XMLHolder holder)
                                throws XMLException,
                                       java.io.IOException
Takes a XMLHolder and converts it to instances of SerializedHolder. Each instance of SerializedHolder contains a well formed XML that (currently) encapsulates either a WSDL or a XML schema.

The 0th element of the return array is always the base WSDL or XML schema. If there are any $lt;import> elements in the XML, the imported XML is encapsulated in the subsequent indexes in the return array.

Takes an XMLHolder and user options and returns an array of SerializedHolders, which contains the byte representation of all the Java classes need for the WSDL2Java functionality
Parameters:
WSDLHolder - a WSDLHolder encapsulating the WSDL to be transformed into Java code
options - User specified options that are needed
Returns:
SerializedHolder[] this array contains the java code to be written to disk

toDeploymentDescriptor

public static SerializedHolder[] toDeploymentDescriptor(WSDLHolder holder,
                                                        java.lang.Class classToConvert,
                                                        Options options)
                                                 throws java.lang.Exception,
                                                        java.io.IOException
Generates a Deployment Descriptor for a WSDLHolder. Each PortType in the WSDLHolder will get its own Deployment Descriptor. The Deployment Descriptor is sent to Parvus SOAP Server when deploying a new service. The Deployment Descriptor is in the form of a XML document. The Name is [PortTypeName].DD
Parameters:
holder - The WSDLHolder used for generating the Deployment Descriptor
classToConvert - Class used to to generate the Deployment Descriptor
options - User entered options
Returns:
SerializedHolder[] this array contains the generated Deployment Descriptor files.
